Anywho, im really bored so i decided to update... Today is World AIDS Day... I found that out on Google.com... :( what a bummer... I made a new sn a few hours ago!! : xVanillaKiss6x Sooo ya... that's it... Oak Park Life = Dullness. I can't get the damn song Drop It Like It's Hot out of my head, haha... i hate having songs stuck in my head... Thanks for reading this really, REALLY boring entry...

Happy Thanksgiving (Really this time) - it wouldn't let me decorate my font Thanksgiving-style :( bummer I woke up at 10:45ish, and my computer is being fixed!! Yay! It turns out we are all cooking :) Alana and my mom are doing most of it, because i seriously SUCK at cooking... but im making this 'apple crisp' thing, Josi made 2 pies, Alana and my mom are making stuffing, the turkey, mashed potatoes, cranberry sauce, deviled eggs and probably more (ahh im gunna gain so much weight, haha) Well, off I go... Have a good turkey day!

ALSO, my pictures: Me givning my graduation speech- taken June 9th 2004 My... face... lol, before going to homecoming- taken October 30th 2004

Happy Thanksgiving!!

Alana and my mom are cooking for tommorrow... just staying home... then going on a serious diet :-P

I was really bored about 15 minutes ago until I got in a fight with someone... you know who you are, and i'm really sorry, i never meant to hurt you.. I IMed you everything i'd repeat here, but again im sorry :(((((

Besides all of that stuff, i have nothing to do this weekend!! (well, besides tommorrow..) So if any of you, unlike most people i know, aren't going out of town, call me to hang out!

**I really dont have much to update, but wow, updating that picture, when i was looking at my pictures from last June... Really depressing... I can't believe how much skinnier i was :( but i have a new pic :)

Oct 30- HOMECOMING WAS SOOOO FUN!  Who says you need a date? :-P  Me, Brittany and Yasmin all met there and had SO MUCH FUN! I even danced, now how weird is that? I *never* dance! It was sooo fun! Anywho, it was like one of the best nights all school year... I can't describe how fun it was!

During the slow dances, me and Cassie were being stupid through most of them.. at the last one, we tangoed through the dance floor, haha. It was funny, because all the couples were like pissed, i guessed we ruined the moment. all well. We (and a few friends) thought is was funny.

Oct 31- I went to Brittany's for breakfast. It was so fun! Some of her relatives were there, her neighbors and Yasmin and her lil bro came. Later on, we got bored and went trick or treating... at like 2PM... it was so funny, obviously people are gunna be like "what the hell?" ... ahh good times...

Then we went to go rent movies, we watched A Cinderella Story, it was awesome :-P (we couldnt watch anything above Pg-13, but that movie was cute.. plus it was easy to make fun of)

That night i did nothing :-P  All well, hehe.


My mom got me a cell phone, i think on the 4th.. and i was so happy!! I take it everywhere with me, not going to lose my phone again... i hope..

Today was kinda boring, i woke up at 10-ish, went on a 2 mile walk on my own (then it rained on me, it was fun)

Well that's all the exciting stuff that happened to me after last entry... later.

I downloaded the Degrassi episode when Manny gets pregnant and to find out apparently us in the USA dont get to see it! It was an old episode! Still pretty good, but sad... and im downloading episodes now from next season, not shown, they are mouth dropping!! 

Anywho, not everyone loves Degrassi... which they SHOULD!!

I decided I am going to homecoming.. why not? I guess i dont need a date, and a lot of my friends dont, so im sure we can have fun :-)

PS: my mood is cause we cant see that episode in the USA and the things are so slow in downloading, haha

My weekend has been pretty good so far...


Friday- after school, I volenteered for the school's haunted house... it was fun, but not that fun, i worked in the kid's area for a bean bag game and not that many people came..

Saturday- volenteered again... THIS TIME IT WAS AWESOME! I got to be a zombie in the haunted house, i looked so different, it was really cool! A lot of my friends were there and i got to meet new people, and get to know some better so it was fun! I scared a few people, surprised many... it was just sooo fun! Even though Cradle Of Filth played for hours straight (the same song) ... lol it was cool though.

Well, today I might hang out with Yasmin, so that should be fun as well :)

That's it for now


PS: I will get new pictures up later, the most recent one is from 8th grade graduation... like 5 months ago (too lazy to actually count haha)
